		<description><![CDATA[On today's Corona Geek Hangout we continued development of our twin stick shooter game with a look at creating a grid based algorithm for smart enemy spawning using physics sensors.]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/uBb-o7qcZsU?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
<p><img class="alignright wp-image-477" src="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/corona-geek-head-transparent-150x150.png" alt="Corona Geek" width="105" height="105" srcset="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/corona-geek-head-transparent-150x150.png 150w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/corona-geek-head-transparent.png 250w" sizes="(max-width: 105px) 100vw, 105px" /> On today&#8217;s Corona Geek Hangout we continued development of our twin stick shooter game with a look at creating a grid based algorithm for smart enemy spawning using <a href=http://github.com/roaminggamer/CoronaGeek/raw/master/Hangouts/Tips_and_Tricks/sensors.zip target="_blank">physics sensors</a>. The also touched on <a href=http://github.com/roaminggamer/CoronaGeek/raw/master/Hangouts/Tips_and_Tricks/objectCaching.zip target="_blank">object caching</a> and it&#8217;s possible benefits.</p>
<p><a href=http://github.com/roaminggamer/CoronaGeek/raw/master/Hangouts/ICanMakeThat/DesktopGames/GeometryWarsClone.zip target="_blank">Download the twin stick shooter project code</a> and make it your own.</p>
